{"id":1265363715,"question_id":13,"lang":"python3","lang_name":"Python3","time":"2Â weeks","timestamp":1716431708,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"46 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/1265363715/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Roman to Integer","memory":"16.4 MB","code":"class Solution:\n    def romanToInt(self, s: str) -> int:\n        values = {\n            \"I\": 1, \n            \"V\": 5,\n            \"X\": 10,\n            \"L\": 50,\n            \"C\": 100,\n            \"D\": 500,\n            \"M\": 1000\n        }\n        combinations = {\n            \"I\": [\"V\", \"X\"],\n            \"X\": [\"L\", \"C\"],\n            \"C\": [\"D\", \"M\"]\n        }\n        nums = []\n        flag = False\n        for idx, char in enumerate(s):\n            if flag:\n                flag = False\n                continue\n            if idx+1 < len(s) and char in combinations.keys() and s[idx+1] in combinations[char]:\n                if char == list(combinations.keys())[0]:\n                    nums.append(values[s[idx+1]]-1)\n                elif char == list(combinations.keys())[1]:\n                    nums.append(values[s[idx+1]]-10)\n                elif char == list(combinations.keys())[2]:\n                    nums.append(values[s[idx+1]]-100)\n                flag = True\n            else:\n                nums.append(values[char])\n            \n        return sum(nums)","compare_result":"","title_slug":"roman-to-integer","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
